ptathlon world record progression}}\n[[File:Ashton Eaton Istanbul 2012.jpg|thumb|World record holder [[Ashton Eaton]] competing at the [[2012 IAAF World Indoor Championships]]]]\n*{{As of|March 2018}}<ref>[http://www.iaaf.org/records/toplists/combined-events/heptathlon/indoor/men/senior Heptathlon \u2013 men \u2013 senior \u2013 indoor]. IAAF. Retrieved on 2014-01-25.</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Score\n!Athlete\n!Date\n!Location\n!Ref\n|-\n!1\n|6645 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Ashton Eaton]]|USA}}\n|9\u201310 March 2012\n|Istanbul\n|\n|-\n!2\n|6479\n|align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Kevin Mayer]]|FRA}}\n|4\u20135 March 2017\n|Belgrade\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Men's Heptathlon Results|url=http://www.european-athletics.org/externalmodules/AT/pdf/ATM700000_C73U.pdf|publisher=[[European Athletics Association|European Athletics]]|date=5 March 2017|accessdate=5 March 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305214525/http://www.european-athletics.org/externalmodules/AT/pdf/ATM700000_C73U.pdf|archivedate=5 March 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n!3\n|6476 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Dan O'Brien]]|USA}}\n|13\u201314 March 1993\n|Toronto\n|\n|-\n!4\n|6438 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Roman \u0160ebrle]]|CZE}}\n|6\u20137 March 2004\n|Budapest\n|\n|-\n!5\n|6424 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Dvo\u0159\u00e1k]]|CZE}}\n|25\u201326 February 2000\n|Ghent\n|\n|-\n!6\n|6418 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Christian Plaziat]]|FRA}}\n|28\u201329 February 1992\n|Genoa\n|\n|-\n!7\n|6415 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Sebastian Chmara]]|POL}}\n|28 February\u20131 March 1998\n|Valencia\n|\n|-\n!8\n|6412 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Lev Lobodin]]|RUS}}\n|7\u20138 February 2003\n|Moscow\n|\n|-\n!9\n|6374 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Erki Nool]]|EST}}\n|6\u20137 March 1999\n|Maebashi\n|\n|-\n!10\n|6372 ||align=left|{{flagathlete|[[Eelco Sintnicolaas]]|NED}}\n|2\u20133 March 2013\n|Gothenburg\n|\n|-\n!11\n|6371\n|align=left|{{flagathlete|